      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:3:54:3",
      "text": [
        " الرَّجُلِ يَتَزَوَّجُ بِغَيْرِ بَيِّنَةٍ قَالَ لَا بَأْسَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazan, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hafs Bin Al Bakhtary, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> regarding the man who married without a proof. He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "3. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from and Muhammad ibn ‘Isma’il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hafs ibn al-Bakhtariy who has said the following: “About the case of a man who marries without witness, abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘It is not unlawful.’” "
        ]
      }
